# HTML Tags Documentation

This documentation categorizes HTML tags based on their usage and semantic purpose. It also lists commonly used attributes.

---

## üìÑ 1. Text Formatting Tags

| Tag        | Description                        |
| ---------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `<p>`      | Paragraph tag                      |
| `<br>`     | Line break (self-closing)          |
| `<hr>`     | Horizontal rule (self-closing)     |
| `<b>`      | Bold text (non-semantic)           |
| `<strong>` | Bold text (semantic: important)    |
| `<i>`      | Italic text (non-semantic)         |
| `<em>`     | Emphasized text (semantic: stress) |
| `<u>`      | Underlined text                    |
| `<mark>`   | Highlighted text                   |
| `<small>`  | Smaller text                       |
| `<sub>`    | Subscript text                     |
| `<sup>`    | Superscript text                   |
| `<ins>`    | Inserted text (underlined)         |
| `<del>`    | Deleted text (strikethrough)       |

---

## üìë 2. Structural & Semantic Tags

| Tag         | Description                        |
| ----------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `<html>`    | Root element                       |
| `<head>`    | Container for metadata             |
| `<title>`   | Title of the document              |
| `<body>`    | Main content container             |
| `<header>`  | Introductory content or navigation |
| `<nav>`     | Navigation links                   |
| `<main>`    | Main content area                  |
| `<section>` | Thematic grouping of content       |
| `<article>` | Self-contained content block       |
| `<aside>`   | Tangential content (like sidebars) |
| `<footer>`  | Footer content                     |
| `<div>`     | Generic container                  |
| `<span>`    | Inline container                   |

---

## üî¢ 3. List Tags

| Tag    | Description                |
| ------ | -------------------------- |
| `<ul>` | Unordered list             |
| `<ol>` | Ordered list               |
| `<li>` | List item                  |
| `<dl>` | Description list           |
| `<dt>` | Term in a description list |
| `<dd>` | Description of the term    |

---

## üßæ 4. Table Tags

| Tag          | Description               |
| ------------ | ------------------------- |
| `<table>`    | Table container           |
| `<tr>`       | Table row                 |
| `<td>`       | Table data cell           |
| `<th>`       | Table header cell         |
| `<thead>`    | Header group of a table   |
| `<tbody>`    | Body group of a table     |
| `<tfoot>`    | Footer group of a table   |
| `<caption>`  | Table title               |
| `<colgroup>` | Grouping of table columns |
| `<col>`      | Column formatting         |

---

## üì∑ 5. Media Tags

| Tag        | Description                                     |
| ---------- | ----------------------------------------------- |
| `<img>`    | Embed image (self-closing)                      |
| `<audio>`  | Embed audio                                     |
| `<video>`  | Embed video                                     |
| `<source>` | Source for media (used in `<audio>`, `<video>`) |
| `<track>`  | Subtitles for media                             |
| `<iframe>` | Embed external content                          |
| `<embed>`  | Embed external application (self-closing)       |
| `<object>` | Embed external resources like Flash             |

---

## üîò 6. Form Tags

| Tag          | Description                     |
| ------------ | ------------------------------- |
| `<form>`     | Form container                  |
| `<input>`    | Input field (self-closing)      |
| `<textarea>` | Multiline input                 |
| `<label>`    | Label for input                 |
| `<button>`   | Clickable button                |
| `<select>`   | Dropdown list                   |
| `<option>`   | Option in dropdown              |
| `<optgroup>` | Grouping of dropdown options    |
| `<fieldset>` | Group related fields            |
| `<legend>`   | Caption for `<fieldset>`        |
| `<datalist>` | Suggestion list for `<input>`   |
| `<output>`   | Output value from a calculation |

---

## üîó 7. Link and Navigation Tags

| Tag      | Description                        |
| -------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `<a>`    | Anchor (hyperlink)                 |
| `<link>` | External resource link (CSS, etc.) |
| `<nav>`  | Navigation menu                    |

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è 8. Meta and Script Tags

| Tag          | Description                        |
| ------------ | ---------------------------------- |
| `<meta>`     | Metadata (charset, viewport, etc.) |
| `<script>`   | Embed or link JavaScript           |
| `<noscript>` | Alternative content for no JS      |
| `<style>`    | Internal CSS                       |
| `<base>`     | Base URL for relative links        |

---

## ‚ö†Ô∏è 9. Deprecated Tags (Not recommended)

| Tag         | Description                    |
| ----------- | ------------------------------ |
| `<center>`  | Center text (use CSS instead)  |
| `<font>`    | Specify font (use CSS instead) |
| `<marquee>` | Scrolling text (deprecated)    |
| `<big>`     | Larger text (use CSS)          |
| `<tt>`      | Teletype text (use CSS)        |

---

## üß© 10. Common HTML Attributes

| Attribute     | Usage                                   |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------- |
| `id`          | Unique identifier                       |
| `class`       | CSS class for styling                   |
| `style`       | Inline CSS                              |
| `title`       | Tooltip text                            |
| `alt`         | Alternate text for images               |
| `src`         | Source file (e.g., images, media)       |
| `href`        | Hyperlink reference                     |
| `name`        | Form element name                       |
| `value`       | Default value for input                 |
| `type`        | Type of input element                   |
| `placeholder` | Placeholder text in input               |
| `readonly`    | Makes input read-only                   |
| `disabled`    | Disables input or element               |
| `checked`     | Pre-check checkbox or radio             |
| `selected`    | Pre-select dropdown option              |
| `required`    | Makes field mandatory                   |
| `action`      | URL form submits to                     |
| `method`      | GET or POST method for form             |
| `target`      | Opens link in new window/tab (`_blank`) |

---

## ‚úÖ Notes

* Semantic tags improve accessibility and SEO.
* Always use attributes relevant to context.
* Prefer CSS for styling and formatting over old HTML tags.

